      "updated": 1770715607377,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Now let’s rebuild your understanding step by step 🧠\n\n1️⃣ WSGI – what really happens\nYour understanding\n\n✔ Correct:\n\nWorkers decided by CPU cores + RAM\nOne request blocks a worker\nIf stuck → worker is useless\n\nGunicorn\n ├── Worker 1 (process)\n ├── Worker 2 (process)\n ├── Worker 3 (process)\n\nEach worker is a separate OS process.\n\nInside one worker:\n\nSingle thread (by default)\nBlocking I/O\nOne request at a time\nWhat happens if a request is slow?\n\nWorker is blocked \nCannot serve another request\nNeed more workers to handle load",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Now let’s rebuild your understanding step by step 🧠\n\n1️⃣ WSGI – what really happens\nYour understanding\n\n✔ Correct:\n\nWorkers decided by CPU cores + RAM\nOne request blocks a worker\nIf stuck → worker is useless\n\nGunicorn\n ├── Worker 1 (process)\n ├── Worker 2 (process)\n ├── Worker 3 (process)\n\nEach worker is a separate OS process.\n\nInside one worker:\n\nSingle thread (by default)\nBlocking I/O\nOne request at a time\nWhat happens if a request is slow?\n\nWorker is blocked \nCannot serve another request\nNeed more workers to handle load",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "ByebjJXEXQugi1OwtFxkC",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1978.7553483576967,
      "y": 7122.031216593081,
      "width": 605,
      "height": 1725,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bEV",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1250483012,
      "version": 58,
      "versionNonce": 233909828,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1770715814670,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "2️⃣ ASGI – what actually changes\nKey difference\n\nConcurrency moves from OS → application level\nInstead of:\n“many processes, one request each”\nWe get:\n“one process, many requests (cooperative multitasking)”\n\nASGI worker internals\n\nGunicorn\n ├── Uvicorn Worker (Process)\n │     ├── Event Loop\n │     │     ├── Request A (await DB)\n │     │     ├── Request B (await HTTP)\n │     │     ├── Request C (await Redis)\n\n\nImportant rule ⚠️\n\nAsync does NOT mean parallel execution\nIt means:\nWhile Request A is waiting (await)\nEvent loop switches to Request B\n\n\n3️⃣ Why async can handle multiple requests in one worker\n\nasync def handler():\n    await fetch_from_db()   # non-blocking\n    await call_external_api()\n    return response\n\n\nRequest A → await DB → pause\nRequest B → await HTTP → pause\nRequest C → await Redis → pause\n\n✔ Single worker\n✔ Multiple in-flight requests\n✔ No OS thread creation\n\n\nThis is the core reason FastAPI feels fast.\n\n\n4️⃣ What async CANNOT do (very important)\n\nIf you do this in ASGI:\n\nasync def handler():\n    while True:\n        pass  # CPU-bound loop\n\n\n❌ Entire event loop blocked\n❌ All requests stuck\n❌ Worse than WSGI\n\n\nRule to remember\n\nAsync is great for I/O, terrible for CPU work\n\nCPU work still needs:\nMultiple processes\nBackground workers\nCelery / task queues",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "2️⃣ ASGI – what actually changes\nKey difference\n\nConcurrency moves from OS → application level\nInstead of:\n“many processes, one request each”\nWe get:\n“one process, many requests (cooperative multitasking)”\n\nASGI worker internals\n\nGunicorn\n ├── Uvicorn Worker (Process)\n │     ├── Event Loop\n │     │     ├── Request A (await DB)\n │     │     ├── Request B (await HTTP)\n │     │     ├── Request C (await Redis)\n\n\nImportant rule ⚠️\n\nAsync does NOT mean parallel execution\nIt means:\nWhile Request A is waiting (await)\nEvent loop switches to Request B\n\n\n3️⃣ Why async can handle multiple requests in one worker\n\nasync def handler():\n    await fetch_from_db()   # non-blocking\n    await call_external_api()\n    return response\n\n\nRequest A → await DB → pause\nRequest B → await HTTP → pause\nRequest C → await Redis → pause\n\n✔ Single worker\n✔ Multiple in-flight requests\n✔ No OS thread creation\n\n\nThis is the core reason FastAPI feels fast.\n\n\n4️⃣ What async CANNOT do (very important)\n\nIf you do this in ASGI:\n\nasync def handler():\n    while True:\n        pass  # CPU-bound loop\n\n\n❌ Entire event loop blocked\n❌ All requests stuck\n❌ Worse than WSGI\n\n\nRule to remember\n\nAsync is great for I/O, terrible for CPU work\n\nCPU work still needs:\nMultiple processes\nBackground workers\nCelery / task queues",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
